      "effects": [],
      "system": {
        "subType": "spell",
        "description": "<p><strong>Duration: Instant</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Range: The caster or a creature touched</strong></p>\n<p>This spell has two uses:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Healing a living subject: </strong>Restores 1d6+1 hit points of damage. This cannot grant more hit points than the subject&rsquo;s normal maximum.</li>\n<li><strong>Curing paralysis:</strong> Paralysing effects are negated.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Reversed: Cause Light Wounds</strong></p>\n<p>Inflicts 1d6+1 hit points of damage to a touched creature. In combat, a melee attack roll is required.</p>",
